Mukherjee Says India in Touch With Counterparts on IMF Succesion

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-05-24T09:08:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/mukherjee-says-india-in-touch-with-counterparts-on-imf-succesion.html
India ’s Finance Minister Pranab Mukherjee comments on the process of finding a candidate to head
the International Monetary Fund. He was speaking to reporters in
 New Delhi  today.  “Normally we decide through a process of consensus
building. But at the same time we shall have to keep in mind the
shareholding, and voting power as per shareholding is also a
relevant factor.  “Therefore keeping all these factors the executive
directors are meeting and exchanging views and I am regularly
being informed about what is happening. I am also in touch with
other finance ministers.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tushar Dhara in New Delhi at 
 tdhara1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephanie Phang at   sphang@bloomberg.net . 